    'terms__incorrect_deposits_title' => '2.6. Handling of incorrect deposits of cryptocurrency',
    'terms__incorrect_deposits_text1' => 'Incorrect deposits can occur if a user does not follow CapitureX\'s instructions for depositing. It may be that a user sends cryptocurrency to a wrong address, such as BTC to a LTC address, or that a user sends a transaction with missing additional information for a cryptocurrencies that require this. Examples of cryptocurrencies that require additional information are XRP and XLM.',
    'terms__incorrect_deposits_text2' => 'CapitureX will not always be able to see where the incorrectly deposited cryptocurrency came from, and it may be very labor-intensive to figure this out. Therefore, CapitureX will only attempt to credit such incorrect deposits if we are informed of the transaction within 10 days of it being sent. This has a fixed price of 5000GBP. Recovering XRP transactions sent without a TAG is also possible, but it incurs a fee of 500GBP. While we cannot guarantee the retrieval of such transactions, we are committed to making our best efforts. Charges will only apply if funds are successfully recovered. The recovery timeframe is variable, and it may take up to 90 days from the reporting date for the funds to be restored.',
    'terms__fiat_money_title' => '2.7. Fiat money',
    'terms__fiat_money_text1' => 'To buy cryptocurrency through our platform, users must have money in their CapitureX account. Each user\'s account is linked to a bank account.',
    'terms__fiat_money_text2' => 'The user decides what the money in the account will be used for. The user can only transfer money from his/her CapitureX account to a UK bank account belonging to the same user. For such a fiat withdrawal to be completed, the user must be able to verify ownership of the bank account he/she wishes to withdraw money to.',
    'terms__fiat_money_text3' => 'Only bank deposits from UK bank accounts are possible. It is a condition that the user owns the bank account the money is transferred from. We may require the user to display valid credentials that the bank account belongs to the user. Money sent from an account not owned by the user will be returned.',
    'terms__fiat_money_text4' => 'Any fraud or attempted fraud will be reported to legal authorities.',
    'terms__fiat_money_text5' => 'See our price list for an overview of the costs for withdrawal of fiat money.',
    'terms__termination_title' => '2.8. Termination of accounts',
    'terms__termination_text1' => 'All users of CapitureX have the right to have their account deleted from the system. All personal information sent to the company by the user is encrypted and stored safely. We are required to store data used in connection with KYC for five years after the customer relationship has been terminated or the last transaction has been completed. User data that we are not required to store will be deleted as soon as possible after the termination of the customer relationship.',
    'terms__termination_text2' => 'The company may block investing and withdrawals from a user account during KYC-investigations. If the system detects that an account is used in connection with illegal activities, such as money laundering or terrorist financing, the system will automatically lock down the account. In these cases, the company reserves the right to report the user to the appropriate legal authorities in the United Kingdom.',
    'terms__termination_text3' => 'The company reserves the right to terminate user accounts without notice for breach of the terms of service. An account will generally not lose any funds even if it is terminated. All assets will be exchanged to GBP and transferred back to the owner\'s bank account as soon as possible. An exception to this is if the authorities have frozen the funds.',
    'terms__buying_selling_title' => '3. Buying and investing',
    'terms__buying_selling_text1' => 'CapitureX charges a fee for investing on the exchange. The user will be able to see the size of this fee before a new order is placed. By buying or selling cryptocurrencies, the user accepts our terms of service.',
    'terms__buying_selling_text2' => 'Investments carried out on the platform are final. The user will is able to see the price that the investment will be carried out at, and in the case of a "limit order", the user can set a limit for the price at which the investment is to be carried out at. In the case of a "market order", the user receives an estimate of price and information on the maximum deviation from this estimate. The user must approve this before the order is executed.',
    'terms__buying_selling_text3' => 'After an investment has been completed, it cannot be reversed, and the company offers no refund if the user wishes to withdraw from an investment after an order is completed.',
    'terms__buying_selling_text4' => 'See our list of fees here.',
    'terms__responsibility_title' => '4. Responsibility and compensation',
    'terms__responsibility_general_title' => '4.1 General',
    'terms__responsibility_general_text1' => 'Buying and selling of cryptocurrencies on CapitureX take place entirely at the users\' own risk. The company will not be liable for any direct or indirect loss the users may experience when investing on our platform.',
    'terms__responsibility_general_text2' => 'This means that the company will not be liable if the users suffer losses in investments, profit, data or damage that may result from technical errors, transaction processing time, processing time for KYC, system failure, interrupted network connections, unforeseen events (such as natural disasters) etc.',
    'terms__responsibility_general_text3' => 'The company works hard to always have our services available to our users. However, we can not guarantee that the platform will be open at all times. In case of downtime or other issues, we will try to keep all our channels open and update our users as soon as possible.',
    'terms__responsibility_general_text4' => 'The company will comply with all applicable laws, regulations, and requirements. The company operates in the United Kingdom and follows UK legislation. We will, therefore, fulfill legal requests from the UK authorities to share user information and lock down user accounts.',
    'terms__responsibility_general_text5' => 'By accepting these terms of service, the user agrees to comply with these terms of service and all applicable laws and regulations.',
    'terms__tax_calculator_title' => '4.2 CapitureX’s tax calculator',
    'terms__tax_calculator_text' => 'CapitureX Enterprises Limited (CapitureX) does not provide tax advice. CapitureX\'s tax calculation is only intended as a non-binding tool for you when you fill in your tax return. CapitureX does not guarantee that the calculations as such are correct or that our understanding of the tax rules as a basis for the calculations is correct. CapitureX cannot be held responsible for any direct or indirect loss and/or damage due to errors in the service itself or for your use of the service. CapitureX cannot be held responsible for loss of access to the service due to technical issues, user errors or any other reason.',
    'terms__staking_title' => '5. Staking',
    'terms__staking_general_title' => '5.1 General',
    'terms__staking_general_text' => 'CapitureX offers staking of certain cryptocurrencies that use proof-of-stake as a consensus mechanism. When a user chooses to stake, the user sets an amount which, with the help of our staking service provider, is used as security to validate transactions and produce blocks, thereby ensuring the operation of a blockchain network. The user can thus obtain a reward in the form of cryptocurrency from the network. The reward varies, e.g. depending on network traffic.',
    'terms__staking_service_title' => '5.2 More about the service',
    'terms__staking_service_text1' => 'CapitureX\'s staking service means that we, or a third party with whom we work, will stake cryptocurrency on your behalf. You will still have ownership of your staked assets. The total earned reward is distributed between users who stake a given cryptocurrency, based on the individual user\'s share of the assets staked at any given time.',
    'terms__staking_service_text2' => 'We will credit your user account with any earned rewards, minus a commission. CapitureX makes no guarantee of reward crediting until the reward has actually been received from the relevant network.',
    'terms__staking_service_text3' => 'Some blockchain networks require staked cryptocurrency to be locked for a certain period of time. In some cases, withdrawal of staked cryptocurrency may be delayed due to protocol or possible network conditions. The applicable terms for each individual cryptocurrency are described before choosing to stake.',
    'terms__staking_service_text4' => 'Some blockchain networks penalize staked assets if the transaction validator representing those assets mistakenly produces a block. This is called "slashing". CapitureX will take reasonable steps to prevent assets that have been staked from being "slashed", but if this should happen, CapitureX will replace your assets at no extra cost, unless the reason for the slashing is:',
    'terms__staking_service_list1' => 'errors at protocol level due to bugs, maintenance,',
    'terms__staking_service_list2' => 'acts or omissions of the service provider,',
    'terms__staking_service_list3' => 'hacking, malicious attack or',
    'terms__staking_service_list4' => 'force majeure events.',
    'terms__staking_service_text5' => 'In some blockchain networks where CapitureX offers staking, the staking happens without locking, relocation, risk of loss of assets or violation of separatist rights. Currently, this applies to Cardano (ADA). In these blockchain networks, all customer funds will be staked. In those cases where the customer chooses not to stake their funds on these blockchain networks, CapitureX will use any profits from such staking to operate the staking services we offer our customers.',
    'terms__staking_tax_title' => '5.3 Tax',
    'terms__staking_tax_text' => 'Reward from staking is taxable income in the year it is earned.',
    'terms__governing_law_title' => '6. Governing law',
    'terms__governing_law_text' => 'The terms of service are subject to UK law. UK courts shall settle disputes concerning the interpretation and application of the terms of service.',
    'terms__change_terms_title' => '7. Change of Terms',
    'terms__change_terms_text' => 'We reserve the right to change these terms of service. By agreeing to the terms of service, you consent us contacting you by email to inform you about important changes.',
    'terms__create_account_button' => 'Create a CapitureX account here',
