    // PRIVACY PAGE
    'privacy__title' => 'Privacy policy',
    'privacy__nav_title' => 'Content',
    'privacy__introduction_title' => '1. Introduction',
    'privacy__introduction_text' => 'This privacy policy describes how your personal information is collected and processed when using CapitureX, and your rights related to the processing of your personal information. CapitureX is owned and operated by CapitureX Enterprises Limited, registered in Malaysia. In this statement, CapitureX Enterprises Limited will be referred to as "CapitureX", or "we". CapitureX is subject to Malaysian law and will process your personal information in accordance with the current privacy legislation.',
    'privacy__data_controller_title' => '2. Data controller',
    'privacy__data_controller_text1' => 'CapitureX is the data controller for your personal information. The data controller is the one who determines the purpose of processing personal information and the processes to be used. The data controller has the ultimate responsibility to ensure that all processing and handling of personal data is in accordance with applicable legislation.',
    'privacy__data_controller_text2' => 'Our full details are: Full name of legal entity: CapitureX Enterprises Limited Registered in Malaysia Contact person: Trang Hoang',
    'privacy__data_controller_text3' => 'Postal address: Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia',
    'privacy__data_controller_text4' => 'If you have questions regarding how we collect and use your data, you can contact us using the contact details above.',
    'privacy__data_controller_text5' => 'We wish to have the information we hold about you accurate and up to date. Please let us know if your personal information changes by updating your user profile.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_title' => '3. What personal information we collect and reason for processing',
    'privacy__collect_reason_text1' => 'When you use our website, create a user profile or contact CapitureX, we will process personal information about you. We collect and use your personal information for different purposes. CapitureX’s processing of personal data is subject to your consent or other legal requirements.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_text2' => 'We process the following personal information for the purposes listed below:',
    'privacy__collect_reason_creation_title' => 'Creation of user Profile:',
    'privacy__collect_reason_creation_text' => 'You can create a user profile on our website to buy and sell cryptocurrencies. The legal basis for processing is the fulfillment of the agreement.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_creation_info_text' => 'When you create such a profile, we will process the following information:',
    'privacy__collect_reason_creation_list1' => 'Identification data such as name, title, date of birth and gender.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_creation_list2' => 'Contact data such as mailing address, email and phone number.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_creation_list3' => 'Financial data such as bank account and card information.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_creation_list4' => 'Transaction data such as time, amount and other information about transfers between you and us.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_creation_list5' => 'Profile data such as username, password, settings, and feedback on surveys.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_creation_list6' => 'Technical data such as login, IP addresses, browser information, language selection, time zone, referral id and digital fingerprints of devices.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_legal_text' => 'When establishing a user profile, there will be several legal requirements that we must follow. Below is a description of various activities where CapitureX stores personal data:',
    'privacy__collect_reason_activity1_title' => 'Activity: Creation of user account.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_activity1_info' => 'Personal information: E-mail, IP addresses, geolocation data, referral id and fingerprints from devices.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_activity1_basis' => 'Basis: Required for login to CapitureX, securing your account as well as complying with anti-money laundering regulations.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_activity2_title' => 'Activity: Upgrade of user profile.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_activity2_info' => 'Personal information: Full name, address, date of birth, nationality and 2-factor token.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_activity2_basis' => 'Basis: Required to comply with anti-money laundering regulations. 2 factor is required to keep your account secure.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_activity3_title' => 'Activity: Identity verification.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_activity3_info' => 'Personal information: Government ID, national identity number.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_activity3_basis' => 'Basis: Required to comply with anti-money laundering regulations.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_activity4_title' => 'Activity: Submitting our KYC questionnaire.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_activity4_info' => 'Personal information: Information about job situation, purpose for creating an account, origin and ownership of funds, future deposits and withdrawals, income and possible political exposure.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_activity4_basis' => 'Basis: Required to comply with anti-money laundering regulations.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_activity5_title' => 'Activity: Logging in to your account.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_activity5_info' => 'Personal information: IP addresses, geolocation data, referral id and fingerprints from devices.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_activity5_basis' => 'Basis: Required for securing your account as well as complying with anti-money laundering regulations.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_activity6_title' => 'Activity: Deposit or withdrawal of fiat.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_activity6_info' => 'Personal information: Information about your bank account and transfers to us.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_activity6_basis' => 'Basis: Required to comply with anti-money laundering regulations. You can only withdraw money from an account that you have ownership of.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_activity7_title' => 'Activity: Deposit or withdrawal of cryptocurrency.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_activity7_info' => 'Personal information: Information about your deposit and withdrawal addresses.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_activity7_basis' => 'Basis: Required to comply with anti-money laundering regulations.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_user_data_title' => 'User data:',
    'privacy__collect_reason_user_data_text' => 'When you use our website and our services, we store information about your use for use in statistics and analyzes. We do this to get a better understanding of how our services are used so that we can improve the quality of them. We process such personal information on the basis of an interest assessment. We have considered it necessary for us to do this so that we can customize the website for our users.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_marketing_title' => 'Marketing:',
    'privacy__collect_reason_marketing_text' => 'We send out newsletters, marketing- and other information about our business by e-mail to you if you have given us your consent. You can withdraw this consent at any time by changing your settings for newsletters in your user profile. If you choose to not receive a newsletter from us, you will not receive information about any competitions and other interesting bonus programs. We will not share your personal information with third parties for use in marketing without your consent.',
    'privacy__collect_reason_provide_text' => 'If you do not wish to provide us the required personal information, we cannot offer you services at CapitureX.',
    'privacy__disclosure_title' => '4. Disclosure of personal information to third parties',
    'privacy__disclosure_text1' => 'We will not disclose your personal information to third parties unless there is a legal basis for such disclosure or it is necessary for us to fulfill our agreement with you. Examples of such a basis will typically be when getting consent from you, if there is a legal basis requiring us to disclose the information (including suspicion of criminal activity), or if it is necessary as a part of the customer control our banking relationships are carrying out with us and/or as part of the customer control your banking relationship carry out of your customer relationship in connection with deposits to or withdrawals from us.',
    'privacy__disclosure_text2' => 'Personal data we process is stored in Malaysia / EEA area.',
    'privacy__security_title' => '5. Data security',
    'privacy__security_text1' => 'We always make adequate technical and organizational measures to ensure that the information is secure. We have security measures that prevent your personal information from being shared, modified, lost or misused otherwise. We only provide employees who need it, access to your personal information. Employees with such access will treat the information confidentially.',
    'privacy__security_text2' => 'We are required by law to inform you if a data breach occurs or any of any other situations occurring where your personal information is at risk. We will do that as quickly as possible.',
    'privacy__storage_title' => '6. Data storage',
    'privacy__storage_text1' => 'We store your personal information as long as necessary for the purpose for which the personal information was collected. Personal data we process to fulfill an agreement with you will be deleted when the agreement is fulfilled, and all obligations arising from the agreement are fulfilled. Duties resulting from the contractual relationship may, for example, be data storage requirements due to accounting laws, anti-money laundering laws or other regulations.',
    'privacy__storage_text2' => 'In cases where we are not required by law to store information, we will save this as long as it is appropriate to provide our services in the best possible way. You can contact us to know what data we have stored about you and ask us to delete data about you.',
    'privacy__rights_title' => '7. Your rights',
    'privacy__rights_text1' => 'You have a number of legal rights in regards to your ownership of personal information we have stored about you and our use of this information.',
    'privacy__rights_text2' => 'You have the right to:',
    'privacy__rights_list1' => 'Receive the personal information we have stored about you.',
    'privacy__rights_list2' => 'Ask to have your personal information changed in case of errors.',
    'privacy__rights_list3' => 'Request to delete your personal information, as long as we are not required by law to store it.',
    'privacy__rights_list4' => 'Complain about the use of your personal information.',
    'privacy__rights_list5' => 'Require that we limit our use of your personal information.',
    'privacy__rights_list6' => 'Ask to transfer your personal information to another service.',
    'privacy__rights_list7' => 'Withdraw your consent regarding our use of your personal information.',
    'privacy__rights_datatilsynet_link' => 'You can read more about your rights on <a href="https://www.ppd.gov.my/">the Personal Data Protection Department Malaysia homepage.</a>.',
    'privacy__rights_contact_link' => 'If you wish to make any of the requests described above, <a href="<?php echo getHref("login") ?>">contact us</a>.',
    'privacy__rights_text3' => 'It is free for you to contact us and make requests regarding your personal information. If requests regarding your personal information are unfounded or excessive, including frequent repetition, we may require a reasonable fee to complete your request. It is also possible that we refuse to comply with your requests in such cases.',
    'privacy__rights_text4' => 'If you want access to information or to make changes to your personal information, we require you to identify yourself. You can, for example, identify yourself using your bank login. In some cases, we may require you to provide additional information in order for us to identify you sufficiently.',
    'privacy__rights_text5' => 'We try to answer all such requests within 30 days. In all cases, we will inform you within 30 days that the request has been received and what the further proceedings will be.',
    'privacy__third_parties_title' => '8. Links to third parties',
    'privacy__third_parties_text' => 'CapitureX’s website, capiturex.cfd, may include links to third-party websites, plug-ins, and applications. Clicking on those links or enabling those connections may allow third parties to collect or share data about you. We do not control these third-party websites and are not responsible for their privacy statements. When you leave our website, we encourage you to read the privacy notice of every website you visit.',
    'privacy__complaints_title' => '9. Complaints',
    'privacy__complaints_text1' => 'If you believe that our processing of personal information does not match what we have described here or in other ways violate privacy laws, you may appeal to the Personal Data Protection Department Malaysia.',
    'privacy__complaints_datatilsynet_link' => 'You can contact <a href="https://www.ppd.gov.my/en/complaint/">the Personal Data Protection Department Malaysia here.</a>.',
    'privacy__cookies_title' => '10. Cookies',
    'privacy__cookies_text' => 'You can set your browser to refuse all or some browser cookies or to alert you when websites place or access cookies. If you disable or refuse cookies, please note that some parts of this website may become inaccessible or not function properly.',
    // TERMS PAGE
    'terms__title' => 'Terms of service',
    'terms__nav_title' => 'Content',
    'terms__general_title' => '1. General',
    'terms__general_text1' => 'These terms of service govern the relationship between you ("user") and CapitureX Enterprises Limited ("the company"). By creating an account on CapitureX or other services related to our company, you confirm that you have read and accepted our current terms of service.',
    'terms__general_text2' => 'CapitureX offers a safe platform for buying and selling cryptocurrencies (such as bitcoin, litecoin, ether, XRP, ada, dai, solana, and polkadot). We support investing between cryptocurrencies and regular currencies (fiat money, such as MYR).',
    'terms__general_text3' => 'In order to use our services, we require that our users are 18 years of age or older, have a valid Malaysian national identity number, and are qualified to enter into legal agreements. We only allow one account per person. The account is personal and should therefore only be used by the registered owner. An account can not be used for investing, transferring or storing funds on behalf of others. If we find that an account does not comply with these requirements, the account will be closed immediately.',
    'terms__accounts_title' => '2. Accounts',
    'terms__accounts_general_title' => '2.1. General',
    'terms__accounts_general_text1' => 'CapitureX is a safe and secure platform for buying and investing in cryptocurrencies. We give our customers the opportunity to buy and sell cryptocurrencies on our platform against fiat money and other cryptocurrencies.',
    'terms__accounts_general_text2' => 'We require 2-factor authentication for all accounts. This is done either with your bank or with a 2-factor authentication app such as Google Authenticator or Authy. Login is done with your bank or e-mail and password.',
    'terms__accounts_general_text3' => 'We recommend that users of CapitureX use a password that has not been used elsewhere. We recommend using a password generator and saving your password in a safe place, such as in a password manager like KeePass, 1Password, Dashlane or LastPass.',
    'terms__accounts_general_text4' => 'The company will not be responsible for theft of the users\' funds due to negligence on the part of the users, including if the user has a weak password or has not stored their verification method and their own cellphone in a secure manner.',
    'terms__crypto_storage_title' => '2.2. Cryptocurrency storage',
    'terms__crypto_storage_text1' => 'The company stores the users\' cryptocurrencies in digital wallets. A digital wallet for cryptocurrency is software specifically developed to send and receive cryptocurrencies. A wallet contains keys that are used to sign transactions and thus send cryptocurrency.',
    'terms__crypto_storage_text2' => 'The company guarantees that the digital wallets are adequately secured. The majority of funds are secured with encryption keys in cold-storage, so users\' funds are protected from theft. Our security system may cause some waiting time for withdrawals during busy hours.',
    'terms__airdrops_title' => '2.3. "Airdrops" and the like',
    'terms__airdrops_text' => 'CapitureX has no control over whether and which "airdrops" etc. are sent to the digital wallets where we hold the customers’ cryptocurrencies. The vast majority of airdropped cryptocurrencies do not meet our requirements to be listed and supported on our exchange. Even if an airdropped cryptocurrency was to meet CapitureX\'s requirements for listing and support, CapitureX has no obligation to credit users for airdrops that have occurred or will occur in the future.',
    'terms__hard_forks_title' => '2.4. "Hard forks"',
    'terms__hard_forks_text1' => '"Forks" are changes in the source code of a cryptocurrency. "Hard forks" add changes to a cryptocurrency that are not compatible with previous versions of the software. This leads to the creation of two different blockchains.',
    'terms__hard_forks_text2' => 'In most cases, protocol changes are planned and accepted by the community without significant disputes, and the new updated blockchain will be dominant shortly after the change has taken place. In such cases, CapitureX will support the new updated blockchain. Any value of cryptocurrency on the old blockchain will be considered "airdrops" and handled as described in paragraph 2.3.',
    'terms__hard_forks_text3' => 'In situations where there is a contested hard fork and it is not clear which of the new blockchains will become dominant, CapitureX will normally support both blockchains, provided both meet our requirements to be listed on our exchange.',
    'terms__crypto_transactions_title' => '2.5. Cryptocurrency transactions',
    'terms__crypto_transactions_text1' => 'When cryptocurrency is deposited or withdrawn, the user is responsible for entering the correct address. After the user has confirmed the transaction, it will not be possible to change the information provided.',
    'terms__crypto_transactions_text2' => 'The company does not allow transfers to and from addresses and entities that the company\'s analysis systems and research provide a convincing indication that are linked to activity in violation of our terms. This applies to activities affected by sanctions, money laundering, terrorist financing, fraud, sale of products / services in violation of Malaysian law, gambling companies without a permit in Malaysia, services/functions that cover or hide origin or destination of the funds, platforms with little or no money laundering routines, pyramid schemes and other types of illegal activity.',
    'terms__crypto_transactions_text3' => 'The company may block withdrawals of cryptocurrencies from accounts based on the company\'s risk assessment of transactions and the customer relationship as a whole.',
    'terms__crypto_transactions_text4' => 'We charge a fee for the withdrawal of cryptocurrency. The withdrawal fees and limits varies depending on the cryptocurrency the user wants to withdraw. These fees and limits may be changed.',
    'terms__incorrect_deposits_title' => '2.6. Handling of incorrect deposits of cryptocurrency',
    'terms__incorrect_deposits_text1' => 'Incorrect deposits can occur if a user does not follow CapitureX\'s instructions for depositing. It may be that a user sends cryptocurrency to a wrong address, such as BTC to a LTC address, or that a user sends a transaction with missing additional information for a cryptocurrencies that require this. Examples of cryptocurrencies that require additional information are XRP and XLM.',
    'terms__incorrect_deposits_text2' => 'CapitureX will not always be able to see where the incorrectly deposited cryptocurrency came from, and it may be very labor-intensive to figure this out. Therefore, CapitureX will only attempt to credit such incorrect deposits if we are informed of the transaction within 10 days of it being sent. This has a fixed price of 5000MYR. Recovering XRP transactions sent without a TAG is also possible, but it incurs a fee of 500MYR. While we cannot guarantee the retrieval of such transactions, we are committed to making our best efforts. Charges will only apply if funds are successfully recovered. The recovery timeframe is variable, and it may take up to 90 days from the reporting date for the funds to be restored.',
    'terms__fiat_money_title' => '2.7. Fiat money',
    'terms__fiat_money_text1' => 'To buy cryptocurrency through our platform, users must have money in their CapitureX account. Each user\'s account is linked to a bank account.',
    'terms__fiat_money_text2' => 'The user decides what the money in the account will be used for. The user can only transfer money from his/her CapitureX account to a Malaysian bank account belonging to the same user. For such a fiat withdrawal to be completed, the user must be able to verify ownership of the bank account he/she wishes to withdraw money to.',
    'terms__fiat_money_text3' => 'Only bank deposits from Malaysian bank accounts are possible. It is a condition that the user owns the bank account the money is transferred from. We may require the user to display valid credentials that the bank account belongs to the user. Money sent from an account not owned by the user will be returned.',
    'terms__fiat_money_text4' => 'Any fraud or attempted fraud will be reported to legal authorities.',
    'terms__fiat_money_text5' => 'See our price list for an overview of the costs for withdrawal of fiat money.',
    'terms__termination_title' => '2.8. Termination of accounts',
    'terms__termination_text1' => 'All users of CapitureX have the right to have their account deleted from the system. All personal information sent to the company by the user is encrypted and stored safely. We are required to store data used in connection with KYC for five years after the customer relationship has been terminated or the last transaction has been completed. User data that we are not required to store will be deleted as soon as possible after the termination of the customer relationship.',
    'terms__termination_text2' => 'The company may block investing and withdrawals from a user account during KYC-investigations. If the system detects that an account is used in connection with illegal activities, such as money laundering or terrorist financing, the system will automatically lock down the account. In these cases, the company reserves the right to report the user to the appropriate legal authorities in Malaysia.',
    'terms__termination_text3' => 'The company reserves the right to terminate user accounts without notice for breach of the terms of service. An account will generally not lose any funds even if it is terminated. All assets will be exchanged to MYR and transferred back to the owner\'s bank account as soon as possible. An exception to this is if the authorities have frozen the funds.',
    'terms__buying_selling_title' => '3. Buying and investing',
    'terms__buying_selling_text1' => 'CapitureX charges a fee for investing on the exchange. The user will be able to see the size of this fee before a new order is placed. By buying or selling cryptocurrencies, the user accepts our terms of service.',
    'terms__buying_selling_text2' => 'Investments carried out on the platform are final. The user will is able to see the price that the investment will be carried out at, and in the case of a "limit order", the user can set a limit for the price at which the investment is to be carried out at. In the case of a "market order", the user receives an estimate of price and information on the maximum deviation from this estimate. The user must approve this before the order is executed.',
    'terms__buying_selling_text3' => 'After an investment has been completed, it cannot be reversed, and the company offers no refund if the user wishes to withdraw from an investment after an order is completed.',
    'terms__buying_selling_text4' => 'See our list of fees here.',
    'terms__responsibility_title' => '4. Responsibility and compensation',
    'terms__responsibility_general_title' => '4.1 General',
    'terms__responsibility_general_text1' => 'Buying and selling of cryptocurrencies on CapitureX take place entirely at the users\' own risk. The company will not be liable for any direct or indirect loss the users may experience when investing on our platform.',
    'terms__responsibility_general_text2' => 'This means that the company will not be liable if the users suffer losses in investments, profit, data or damage that may result from technical errors, transaction processing time, processing time for KYC, system failure, interrupted network connections, unforeseen events (such as natural disasters) etc.',
    'terms__responsibility_general_text3' => 'The company works hard to always have our services available to our users. However, we can not guarantee that the platform will be open at all times. In case of downtime or other issues, we will try to keep all our channels open and update our users as soon as possible.',
    'terms__responsibility_general_text4' => 'The company will comply with all applicable laws, regulations, and requirements. The company operates in Malaysia and follows Malaysian legislation. We will, therefore, fulfill legal requests from the Malaysian authorities to share user information and lock down user accounts.',
    'terms__responsibility_general_text5' => 'By accepting these terms of service, the user agrees to comply with these terms of service and all applicable laws and regulations.',
    'terms__tax_calculator_title' => '4.2 CapitureX’s tax calculator',
    'terms__tax_calculator_text' => 'CapitureX Enterprises Limited (CapitureX) does not provide tax advice. CapitureX\'s tax calculation is only intended as a non-binding tool for you when you fill in your tax return. CapitureX does not guarantee that the calculations as such are correct or that our understanding of the tax rules as a basis for the calculations is correct. CapitureX cannot be held responsible for any direct or indirect loss and/or damage due to errors in the service itself or for your use of the service. CapitureX cannot be held responsible for loss of access to the service due to technical issues, user errors or any other reason.',
    'terms__staking_title' => '5. Staking',
    'terms__staking_general_title' => '5.1 General',
    'terms__staking_general_text' => 'CapitureX offers staking of certain cryptocurrencies that use proof-of-stake as a consensus mechanism. When a user chooses to stake, the user sets an amount which, with the help of our staking service provider, is used as security to validate transactions and produce blocks, thereby ensuring the operation of a blockchain network. The user can thus obtain a reward in the form of cryptocurrency from the network. The reward varies, e.g. depending on network traffic.',
    'terms__staking_service_title' => '5.2 More about the service',
    'terms__staking_service_text1' => 'CapitureX\'s staking service means that we, or a third party with whom we work, will stake cryptocurrency on your behalf. You will still have ownership of your staked assets. The total earned reward is distributed between users who stake a given cryptocurrency, based on the individual user\'s share of the assets staked at any given time.',
    'terms__staking_service_text2' => 'We will credit your user account with any earned rewards, minus a commission. CapitureX makes no guarantee of reward crediting until the reward has actually been received from the relevant network.',
    'terms__staking_service_text3' => 'Some blockchain networks require staked cryptocurrency to be locked for a certain period of time. In some cases, withdrawal of staked cryptocurrency may be delayed due to protocol or possible network conditions. The applicable terms for each individual cryptocurrency are described before choosing to stake.',
    'terms__staking_service_text4' => 'Some blockchain networks penalize staked assets if the transaction validator representing those assets mistakenly produces a block. This is called "slashing". CapitureX will take reasonable steps to prevent assets that have been staked from being "slashed", but if this should happen, CapitureX will replace your assets at no extra cost, unless the reason for the slashing is:',
    'terms__staking_service_list1' => 'errors at protocol level due to bugs, maintenance,',
    'terms__staking_service_list2' => 'acts or omissions of the service provider,',
    'terms__staking_service_list3' => 'hacking, malicious attack or',
    'terms__staking_service_list4' => 'force majeure events.',
    'terms__staking_service_text5' => 'In some blockchain networks where CapitureX offers staking, the staking happens without locking, relocation, risk of loss of assets or violation of separatist rights. Currently, this applies to Cardano (ADA). In these blockchain networks, all customer funds will be staked. In those cases where the customer chooses not to stake their funds on these blockchain networks, CapitureX will use any profits from such staking to operate the staking services we offer our customers.',
    'terms__staking_tax_title' => '5.3 Tax',
    'terms__staking_tax_text' => 'Reward from staking is taxable income in the year it is earned.',
    'terms__governing_law_title' => '6. Governing law',
    'terms__governing_law_text' => 'The terms of service are subject to Malaysian law. Malaysian courts shall settle disputes concerning the interpretation and application of the terms of service.',
    'terms__change_terms_title' => '7. Change of Terms',
    'terms__change_terms_text' => 'We reserve the right to change these terms of service. By agreeing to the terms of service, you consent us contacting you by email to inform you about important changes.',
    'terms__create_account_button' => 'Create a CapitureX account here',
